Titolo: Revenge of the Beefsteak Tomatoes

Anno: 1983

Descrizione: Revenge of the Beefsteak Tomatoes is a video game for the Atari 2600 written by John Russell, and published by Fox Video Games, Inc. in 1983. Upon its release in 1983, the game cost roughly $30.The back of the box reads "Perhaps it was a form of protest against bottled Ketchup, or maybe they were provoked by acid rain." However they came into awareness, tomatoes have become killers that cannot be destroyed by mankind's weapons. The tomatoes can only be trapped by building a brick wall.It is believed that title and the concept of this game are inspired by the cult movie Attack of the Killer Tomatoes.

Genere: Non specificato


Valutazione: N/A
